<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium fusisporum" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="fusisporum">Microthecium fusisporum</taxonomicName>
is related to 
<taxonomicName genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. nectrioides" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="nectrioides">Mi. nectrioides</taxonomicName>
, both possessing ostiolate ascomata and smooth-walled ascospores. However, 
<taxonomicName genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. nectrioides" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="nectrioides">Mi. nectrioides</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the absence of the crown of setae around the ostiole and its citriform ascospores, being fusiform in 
<taxonomicName genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. fusisporum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="fusisporum">Mi. fusisporum</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
